column7:
SCENTED CANDLE - TRANO MAPOCH

Mint Leaves - Vetiver Roots - Ylang Ylang

Item Description

The Mabhokho scented candle bears the name of the village in which the Ndebele tradition lives on. The beige and black raffia hand crocheted by Malagasy women is covered with geometric patterns in bold, fashionable colours. The Mabhokho candle with its contemporary tribal look is set to become a coveted interior design object. Its vetiver and mint scent will transport you straight to summer. A portion of sales will be donated to the Mikea people, to publicise their situation.

Item Care Instructions

Always burn your candle until the whole surface becomes liquid. This step may take a long time, especially during the first burning. When the entire top of the wax is liquid, do not burn it longer than one hour. The top layer of liquid wax should never exceed one centimeter in height. Never burn your candle more than the maximum burning time indicated in the candle_Ñés instructions. Never burn it down totally and systematically leave one centimeter at the bottom.

Made in Belgium
MAX 24: 400h ; MAX 35: 800h
MAX 24: 5 ; MAX 35: 7

FRAGRANCE DIFFUSER - MANOU

Mint Leaves - Vetiver Roots - Ylang Ylang

Item Description

The Manou fragrance diffuser is covered with beighe raffia. Its scent made up of notes of vetiver and ylang ylan is a reminder that the Mikea territory in Madagascar once extended all the way to the banks of the stunning Mozambique canal. A portion of sales will be donated to the Mikea people, to publicise their situation.

Item Care Instructions

Place the reed sticks inside the lodge of the diffuser until the fragrance diffusion occurs. For a more intense perfume diffusion, revert the sticks every so often to further diffuse the scent.

Made in Belgium
500 ml 16.91 fl oz
